The basement of the Federal Ministry of Finance was gutted by fire on Wednesday morning. The fire broke out in a room housing inverter batteries in the basement. The fire was put out by the security men on duty before men of the Federal Fire Service arrived the ministry. Special Adviser, Media and Communications to the Minister of Finance Yunusa Tanko Abdullahi confirmed the incident.   News Analysis: Will Russia’s Ukraine invasion push up oil…     Gunmen kidnap doctor on duty in Akwa Ibom     2023 president: APC zoning tilts ticket in South’s favour   - Advertisement - He said the fire was caused by a spark in the room containing inverter batteries. According to him: “The fire was quickly put out before men if the Fire Service got to the ministry”. When The Nation got the Ministry of Finance, normalcy had been restored as workers drove into the building after being searched by security men.